obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25763)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25763&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Handlooms (Reservation`
  line `of Articles for Production) Act, 1985.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 31st March, 1986, vide notification No. G.S.R 505(E), dated 10th March, 1986, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25764)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25764&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Advisory Committee" means the Advisory Committee constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "handloom" means any loom, other than power loom;`
  line
  line `(c) "manufacturer" includes the producer and processor, and the expression "manufacture" shall`
  line `be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(d) "power loom" means a loom which is worked by power as defined in clause (g) of section 2`
  line `of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(e) "processor" means a person engaged in any ancillary process subsequent to the production of`
  line `cloth, such as dyeing, bleaching, mercerising, calendering, embroidering, printing, raising, cloth`
  line `embossing or any other finishing process, but does not include a producer, and the expression`
  line `"process" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(f) "producer" means a person engaged in the production of cloth on any loom, other than`
  line `handloom, and shall include a person who owns, works or operates on, a loom for the production of`
  line `cloth, and the expression produce shall be construed accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25765)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to specify articles for exclusive production by handlooms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25765&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951), the Central`
  line `Government may, if it is satisfied, after considering the recommendations made to it by the Advisory`
  line `Committee, that it is necessary so to do for the protection and development of the handloom industry, by`
  line `order published in the Official Gazette, direct, from time to time, that any article or class of articles shall,`
  line `on and from such date as may be specified in the order (hereinafter referred to as the date of reservation),`
  line `be reserved for exclusive production by handlooms.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order published under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25766)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25766&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, with a view to`
  line `determining the nature of any article or class of articles that may be reserved for exclusive production by`
  line `handlooms, constitute an Advisory Committee consisting of such persons as have, in the opinion of that`
  line `Government, the necessary expertise to give advice on the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Committee shall, after considering the following matters, communicate its`
  line `recommendations to the Central Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the article or class of articles which is being produced by handlooms for mass consumption;`
  line
  line `(b) the article or class of articles which is being produced traditionally by handlooms;`
  line
  line `(c) the level of employment likely to be generated by the production of the article or class of`
  line `articles referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) exclusively by handlooms;`
  line
  line `(d) the protection of interests of persons engaged in the handloom industry and the need for the`
  line `continued maintenance of the industry; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as the Advisory Committee may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25767)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of production of articles exclusively reserved for handlooms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25767&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where an order has`
  line `been made under section 3 reserving any article or class of articles for exclusive production by`
  line `handlooms, such article or class of articles shall not, on and from the date of reservation, be produced by`
  line `any loom, other than handloom:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person who, immediately before the date of reservation of any article or class of`
  line `articles, was engaged in the production of such article or class of articles in any loom, other than`
  line `handloom may continue to be so engaged till the expiry of three months from the date of such reservation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25768)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to call for information or to furnish samples.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25768&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `order, require any manufacturer to furnish, for the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) such information in his possession with respect to any manufacturing activity or business`
  line `carried on by him or by any other person to any officer or authority specified by it in such form and`
  line `within such period as may be specified by that Government in the order;`
  line
  line `(b) such samples of any articles manufactured by him or by any other person for inspection by`
  line `such officer or authority, at such places and within such period as may be specified by it in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any order has been issued to any manufacturer under sub-section (1), he shall comply with`
  line `such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25769)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to enter and impact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25769&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Any officer authorised by the Central Government (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the authorised officer) may enter, at all reasonable times, any place or premises of any`
  line `manufacturer in which any textile articles are stored, kept or exposed for sale and may require the`
  line `production for inspection of any books of account, registers, records or other documents kept therein and`
  line `ask for such information relating to the manufacture, storage or keeping for sale of any such articles or to`
  line `any power looms that may be found in such place as he may think fit for the purposes of carrying into`
  line `effect the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25770)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to search and seize.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25770&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the authorised officer has any reason to believe that,--`
  line
  line `(a) any article or class of articles specified in any order made under section 3 is being produced in`
  line `any place in contravention of such order; or`
  line
  line `(b) any article or class of articles produced in contravention of such order are secreted in any`
  line `place; or`
  line
  line `(c) any article or class of articles is liable to forfeiture under this Act,`
  line
  line `he may enter into and search such place or premises for such article, or class of articles or any powerloom`
  line `which in the opinion of the authorised officer may have been used for the production of such article or`
  line `class of articles.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, as a result of any search made under sub-section (1), any article or class of articles or any`
  line `power loom has been found and the authorised officer has reason to believe that such article or class of`
  line `articles has been produced, or such power loom has been used for the production of any article or class of`
  line `articles, in contravention of any order made under section 3, he may seize such article, class of articles or`
  line `power loom, together with the package, covering or receptacle, if any, in which such article or class of`
  line `articles is found:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to seize any article or power loom, the authorised officer may`
  line `serve on the owner of the article or the power loom, as the case may be, an order that he shall not remove,`
  line `part with, or otherwise deal with, the article or power loom except with the previous permission of such`
  line `authorised officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any article or power loom is seized under sub-section (2) and no prosecution has been`
  line `launched within six months of such seizure, it shall be returned to the person from whose possession it`
  line `was seized.`
  line
  line `(4) The authorised officer may also seize any documents or things which, in his opinion, will be`
  line `useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The person from whose custody any documents are seized under sub-section (4) shall be entitled`
  line `to make copies thereof or takes extracts therefrom in the presence of the authorised officer.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person legally entitled to the documents or things seized under sub-section (4) objects, for`
  line `any reason, to the retention by the authorised officer of the documents or things, he may make an`
  line `application to the Central Government stating therein the reasons for such objection and requesting for the`
  line `return of the documents or things.`
  line
  line `(7) On receipt of an application under sub-section (6), the Central Government may, after giving the`
  line `applicant an opportunity of being heard, pass such order as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25771)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Search and seizure to be made in accordance with the Code of Criminal Procedure,1973.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25771&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches and seizures`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to every search or seizure made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25772)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Penalty for contravention of orders made under section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25772&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Whoever produces any article or`
  line `class of articles in contravention of an order made under section 3,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees per loom by which the said article or class of articles is`
  line `produced, or with both, and in the case of a continuing contravention, with an additional fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees per loom for every day during which such contravention continues`
  line `after conviction for the first such contravention; and`
  line
  line `(b) the article or class of articles in respect of which the order has been contravened or any power`
  line `loom by the use of which such order is contravened, including any package, covering or receptacle in`
  line `which the article or class of articles is found, shall be forfeited to the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the court is of opinion that it is not necessary to direct forfeiture in respect of any`
  line `of the articles, power loom or any package, covering or receptacle, it may, for reasons to be recorded,`
  line `refrain from doing so.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25773)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `False statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25773&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `If any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) when required by any order made under section 6 to furnish any information or sample, makes`
  line `any statement or furnishes any information which is false in any material particular and which he`
  line `knows, or has reasonable cause to believe, to be false or does not believe it to be true, or fails to`
  line `furnish such sample or damages or destroys any article from which such sample was required; or`
  line
  line `(b) when required by the authorised officer under section 7 to produce any books of account,`
  line `registers, records or other documents, fails to produce, or damages or destroys any such books,`
  line `registers or other documents,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25774)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Attempts and abetment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25774&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any person who attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of`
  line `any order made under section 3 shall be deemed to have contravened that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25775)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25775&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a cooperative society registered or`
  line `deemed to be registered under any law for the time being in force, a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25776)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25776&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every offence punishable under this Act shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25777)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25777&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order, direct that the powers exercisable`
  line `by it under any provision of this Act, other than the power to make orders under section 3 or under section`
  line `18 or to make rules under section 19, shall in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions, if`
  line `any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercisable also by--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) such State Government or such officer or authority subordinate to a State Government,`
  line
  line `as may be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25778)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25778&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions as it may consider necessary to a State Government as to the carrying into execution of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25779)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25779&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, State Government or any officer or employee of the Central`
  line `Government or of any State Government or any authorised officer for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or an order made under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25780)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25780&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that the demand for any article or`
  line `class of articles reserved by an order under section 3 outside India is such that it is not possible for the`
  line `handloom industry to meet such demand or any such article or class of articles is required to be produced`
  line `for purposes of research or for the development of markets for such article or class of articles or of the`
  line `handloom industry generally, it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, exempt such article or class of articles from the operation of such order, and permit such`
  line `article or class of articles to be produced by any power loom solely for the purposes of export or for`
  line `research by such institutions as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25781)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816&sectionId=25781&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00013_198522_1517807326816
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
